{"id": "2026-07-11-news-trump-threatens-to-completely-decimate-iran-as-c", "date": "2026-07-11", "stream": "news", "headline": "Trump threatens to 'completely decimate' Iran as ceasefire collapses over Hormuz attacks", "summary": "Trump warned of 1000 missiles and threatened to destroy Iran after assassination-plot reports and Khamenei funeral chants; the US struck five provinces while Hormuz and nuclear talks continued.", "url": "https://www.timesofisrael.com/liveblog-july-11-2026/", "source_domain": "timesofisrael.com", "tier": "T1", "tags": ["ongoing"], "topics": ["geopolitics"], "importance": 3, "display_body": "Trump threatened to \"completely decimate and destroy\" Iran on Saturday 11 July, days after a fragile ceasefire collapsed into fresh US airstrikes. On his Truth Social platform Trump wrote that \"1000 Missiles are Locked and Loaded and aimed at the Islamic Republic of Iran,\" warning of retaliation should Tehran act on a reported plot to assassinate him. Trump declared the June truce over after Iranian attacks on Gulf tankers near the Strait of Hormuz on Wednesday 8 July triggered two nights of US strikes across five Iranian provinces and Iranian counter-strikes on US-linked facilities. Yet talks continue in parallel: Washington is demanding Iran publicly declare the strait open and hand over its stock of more than 900 pounds of highly enriched uranium under a June memorandum of understanding, while Qatari, Omani and Pakistani mediators shuttle between the sides.", "why": "A US president is openly threatening to destroy a country even as satellite imagery suggests Iran is repairing its bombed nuclear sites; the ceasefire exists only on paper, and a wider war is one incident away.", "thread_id": "2026-06-20-cyber-papers-iran-closes-strait-of-hormuz-again-over-israeli", "first_seen_date": "2026-06-20", "event_date": "2026-07-08", "embedding_model": "bge-m3", "emb": ""}
{"id": "2026-07-11-news-russia-strikes-four-kyiv-districts-with-ballisti", "date": "2026-07-11", "stream": "news", "headline": "Russia strikes four Kyiv districts with ballistic missiles and 121 drones, injuring at least 10", "summary": "An overnight Russian bombardment hit four Kyiv districts before sirens sounded on 11 July, wounding at least 10-11 people including a child amid depleted air defences.", "url": "https://euromaidanpress.com/2026/07/11/russian-missiles-strike-four-kyiv-districts-before-air-raid-siren-sounds-injuring-10/", "source_domain": "euromaidanpress.com", "tier": "T1", "tags": ["ongoing", "new source"], "topics": ["geopolitics"], "importance": 2, "display_body": "Russia struck four districts of Kyiv with ballistic missiles and a 121-drone swarm overnight into Saturday 11 July, injuring at least 10-11 people including an 11-year-old boy. The first explosions hit at 03:38, roughly a minute and a half before the city's air-raid sirens sounded at 03:40. Ukraine's air force said Russia fired six Iskander-M/S-400 ballistic missiles, all of which breached the city's defences, alongside six cruise missiles and 121 drones, of which defenders downed 111 drones and two cruise missiles; crews have reportedly switched Patriot batteries to manual mode to ration dwindling interceptor stocks. More than 60 people have been killed across Kyiv since the start of July.", "why": "Kyiv's shield is thinning; air defenders are stretching depleted Western interceptors while Russia intensifies its assault, and the gap between incoming fire and what can be stopped keeps widening as promised aid lags.", "thread_id": "2026-05-20-cyber-papers-russia-ukraine-largest-aerial-campaign-of-the-wa", "first_seen_date": "2026-05-20", "event_date": "2026-07-06", "embedding_model": "bge-m3", "emb": ""}
{"id": "2026-07-11-news-china-evacuates-over-600-000-as-typhoon-bavi-nea", "date": "2026-07-11", "stream": "news", "headline": "China evacuates over 600,000 as Typhoon Bavi nears Zhejiang landfall", "summary": "More than 600,000 people were evacuated in Zhejiang and Fujian on 11 July as weakened but dangerous Typhoon Bavi neared landfall near Wenzhou.", "url": "https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2026/7/11/hundreds-of-thousands-evacuated-as-typhoon-bavi-barrels-towards-china", "source_domain": "aljazeera.com", "tier": "T2", "tags": ["ongoing", "single-source"], "topics": ["world"], "importance": 2, "display_body": "China evacuated more than 600,000 people on Saturday 11 July as Typhoon Bavi approached, with landfall expected near Wenzhou early Sunday 12 July. Authorities moved over half a million residents in eastern Zhejiang province and another 100,000 in neighbouring Fujian, issued an orange alert (the second-highest on a four-level scale), cancelled hundreds of flights and suspended rail, ferry and school services. Bavi has weakened from super-typhoon strength since it tore through the US Pacific islands and killed at least 15 in the Philippines, but forecasters warn its heavy rain bands still pose a serious flooding risk.", "why": "", "thread_id": "2026-07-10-news-typhoon-bavi-forces-taiwan-evacuations-after-15", "first_seen_date": "2026-07-10", "event_date": "2026-07-11", "embedding_model": "bge-m3", "emb": ""}
{"id": "2026-07-11-news-indonesia-s-top-anti-graft-prosecutor-quits-afte", "date": "2026-07-11", "stream": "news", "headline": "Indonesia's top anti-graft prosecutor quits after police seize 74kg gold and $20m cash", "summary": "Febrie Adriansyah resigned as Indonesia's special-crimes head prosecutor on 11 July after raids tied to a blackout-linked corruption probe seized gold and cash.", "url": "https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2026/7/11/indonesias-anti-graft-prosecutor-quits-after-police-seize-gold-and-cash", "source_domain": "aljazeera.com", "tier": "T2", "tags": ["single-source"], "topics": ["politics", "world"], "importance": 1, "display_body": "Indonesia's top anti-corruption prosecutor resigned on Saturday 11 July after police raids seized 74 kg of gold bars and about $20m in cash. Febrie Adriansyah stepped down as head prosecutor for special crimes \"to maintain the integrity, objectivity and neutrality of law enforcement,\" the Attorney General's Office said; he has not been formally charged. Police raided at least 12 locations on 8-9 July in a bribery investigation authorities link to recent nationwide blackouts and to the long-running Asabri and Jiwasraya state-insurer fraud scandals.", "why": "The official meant to lead Indonesia's prosecution of graft is now himself at the centre of a corruption probe, a direct blow to public trust in the institution.", "thread_id": "2026-07-11-news-indonesia-s-top-anti-graft-prosecutor-quits-afte", "first_seen_date": "2026-07-11", "event_date": "2026-07-11", "embedding_model": "bge-m3", "emb": ""}
{"id": "2026-07-11-news-french-minister-faults-switzerland-s-closure-fro", "date": "2026-07-11", "stream": "news", "headline": "French minister faults Switzerland's 'closure from the start' on G7 Evian as Geneva bill hits 31.6M CHF", "summary": "French minister Eleonore Caroit publicly criticised Swiss reticence over June's G7 at Evian on 10 July; Geneva's security cost reached 31.6 million francs with no cost-sharing deal.", "url": "https://www.letemps.ch/suisse/geneve/il-y-a-eu-une-fermeture-des-le-depart-sur-le-g7-une-ministre-francaise-cible-le-manque-de-confiance-avec-la-suisse", "source_domain": "letemps.ch", "tier": "T1", "tags": ["ongoing", "single-source"], "topics": ["switzerland", "politics"], "importance": 2, "display_body": "A French minister publicly faulted Switzerland for \"a closure from the start\" over June's G7 summit at Evian, in remarks in Geneva on Friday 10 July. Eleonore Caroit, France's minister for the Francophonie and international partnerships, said Bern and Geneva had seen only \"costs and potential downsides\" rather than an opportunity to showcase International Geneva. No cost-sharing deal was reached, unlike the 2003 G8 when France reimbursed most of Switzerland's expenses; collaboration is now governed by a 2008 accord. Geneva State Councillor Carole-Anne Kast had earlier put the canton's security bill at 31.6 million francs, and warned the dispute could weigh on regional relations with neighbouring French authorities.", "why": "It is a rare public spat between Paris and Bern over who pays for a summit staged just across the border, friction in exactly the cross-border relationship that shapes daily life in French-speaking Switzerland.", "thread_id": "2026-07-08-news-geneva-says-june-s-g7-at-evian-cost-the-canton-3", "first_seen_date": "2026-07-08", "event_date": "2026-07-10", "embedding_model": "bge-m3", "emb": ""}
{"id": "2026-07-11-news-zurich-svp-picks-rickli-and-hubscher-for-2027-ca", "date": "2026-07-11", "stream": "news", "headline": "Zurich SVP picks Rickli and Hubscher for 2027 cantonal government elections", "summary": "Zurich's SVP named cantonal councillor Natalie Rickli and National Councillor Martin Hubscher as its ticket for the 2027 cantonal government race at a 9 July delegates' assembly.", "url": "https://www.letemps.ch/suisse/suisse-alemanique/a-zurich-l-udc-parie-sur-natalie-rickli-et-martin-hubscher-pour-les-elections-cantonales-2027", "source_domain": "letemps.ch", "tier": "T2", "tags": ["single-source"], "topics": ["switzerland", "politics"], "importance": 1, "display_body": "Zurich's SVP (UDC, the right-wing Swiss People's Party) named its ticket for the 2027 cantonal government elections at a delegates' assembly on Thursday evening 9 July. The party picked sitting cantonal councillor Natalie Rickli, who holds the health portfolio, and Winterthur National Councillor Martin Hubscher. With rival parties' likely candidates already known, the choice sets an early marker in the race for the canton's executive.", "why": "", "thread_id": "2026-07-11-news-zurich-svp-picks-rickli-and-hubscher-for-2027-ca", "first_seen_date": "2026-07-11", "event_date": "2026-07-09", "embedding_model": "bge-m3", "emb": ""}
{"id": "2026-07-11-news-house-explosion-in-leontica-ticino-injures-three", "date": "2026-07-11", "stream": "news", "headline": "House explosion in Leontica, Ticino, injures three police officers", "summary": "Three officers were lightly injured on 10 July when a house exploded as police approached a femicide suspect in Leontica, Ticino; remains and explosives were found in the rubble.", "url": "https://www.srf.ch/news/schweiz/einsatz-am-freitagabend-polizisten-verletzt-bei-explosion-in-einem-haus-in-leontica-ti", "source_domain": "srf.ch", "tier": "T1", "tags": ["single-source"], "topics": ["switzerland"], "importance": 1, "display_body": "Three police officers were lightly injured on Friday evening 10 July when a house exploded in Leontica, Ticino, about 30 km north of Bellinzona. Officers were approaching a man suspected, according to Ticino broadcaster RSI, of killing his ex-wife the previous evening; after a report of gunshots from the home, the building exploded, caught fire and was completely destroyed. Prosecutors and cantonal police said human remains and explosives were found in the rubble, and the man's fate remains unclear.", "why": "", "thread_id": "2026-07-11-news-house-explosion-in-leontica-ticino-injures-three", "first_seen_date": "2026-07-11", "event_date": "2026-07-10", "embedding_model": "bge-m3", "emb": ""}
{"id": "2026-07-11-news-meteoswiss-extends-heat-warning-until-at-least-t", "date": "2026-07-11", "stream": "news", "headline": "MeteoSwiss extends heat warning until at least Thursday 16 July", "summary": "MeteoSwiss extended its heat warning until at least 16 July from Monday 13 July across northern Switzerland, Ticino and Valais, prompting fire bans and water-saving measures.", "url": "https://www.srf.ch/news/schweiz/hitzewelle-im-ticker-hitzewelle-dauert-bis-mindestens-donnerstag-an", "source_domain": "srf.ch", "tier": "T1", "tags": ["single-source"], "topics": ["switzerland", "health"], "importance": 1, "display_body": "MeteoSwiss extended its heat warning until at least Thursday 16 July, effective from Monday 13 July across much of northern Switzerland plus Ticino and Valais. The federal weather service widened the alert as cantons tighten precautions: Fribourg has stiffened its fire ban, the Wil (SG) region is urging water conservation, five streams in Baselland have been fished out over drought, and Zurich is letting construction crews start at 6am. Neighbouring France is activating emergency cooling plans in its hardest-hit departements, and a wildfire in Spain's Andalusia has killed 12.", "why": "It translates directly into rules and precautions for anyone in Switzerland next week: fire bans, water limits and work-hour shifts.", "thread_id": "2026-07-11-news-meteoswiss-extends-heat-warning-until-at-least-t", "first_seen_date": "2026-07-11", "event_date": "2026-07-11", "embedding_model": "bge-m3", "emb": ""}
